HEADWORD: Phase splitting
<hw>Phase splitting</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The dephasing of the
two parts of a single alternating current in two dissimilar branches of
a given circuit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

